==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iulus
<hw>I*u"lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., down, Gr. <?/
down, centipede.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of chilognathous
myriapods. The body is long and round, consisting of numerous smooth,
equal segments, each of which bears two pairs of short legs. It includes
the galleyworms. See <er>Chilognatha</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ivan Ivanovitch</ent>⟦br⟧
